Here comes my niece.

515
00:58:28,965 --> 00:58:31,832
Here comes my niece.

516
00:58:33,970 --> 00:58:36,837
Here comes my niece.
I must present myself.

517
00:58:36,973 --> 00:58:39,840
I must present myself.

518
00:58:39,976 --> 00:58:42,843
I must present myself.

519
00:58:42,979 --> 00:58:45,948
Present! Present! Present!

520
01:02:12,989 --> 01:02:14,957
Is that for me?

521
01:02:16,993 --> 01:02:20,861
- Your uncle is calling your friend.
- Giulio!

522
01:02:20,997 --> 01:02:24,865
- He asked for me?
- At school, they draw with a...

523
01:02:25,001 --> 01:02:27,868
...computer like this one.
You were the best at drawing...

524
01:02:28,004 --> 01:02:29,869
...and you're going to keep on
being the best.

525
01:02:30,006 --> 01:02:32,966
What's this?

526
01:02:32,967 --> 01:02:35,966
They told me that this diskette
explains everything.

527
01:02:37,013 --> 01:02:37,980
Ah, cool.

528
01:02:41,017 --> 01:02:42,882
- You're happy, eh?
- Yep.

529
01:02:43,019 --> 01:02:45,988
Tell your dad.

530
01:02:49,025 --> 01:02:51,994
Yes, of course.

531
01:02:59,035 --> 01:03:03,836
Vincenzo, do you think I'll
win the dance contest?

532
01:03:03,973 --> 01:03:05,941
Another night without dinner!

533
01:03:12,982 --> 01:03:16,850
Follow the lines of Giotto's
drawing with the pencil.

534
01:03:16,986 --> 01:03:21,946
Then remove it, and obtain the
graphical copy.

535
01:03:23,993 --> 01:03:25,961
Later...

536
01:03:33,002 --> 01:03:36,870
Why do they teach you to
draw trees like that?

537
01:03:37,006 --> 01:03:40,965
I like drawing people more, too.

538
01:03:42,011 --> 01:03:43,876
Look at this.

539
01:03:44,013 --> 01:03:48,882
They're strangers too.
The professor was right.

540
01:03:49,018 --> 01:03:52,886
He says that if you copy them
well enough...

541
01:03:53,022 --> 01:03:56,890
...then you end up really
knowing these men.

542
01:03:57,026 --> 01:04:00,894
All the lines in the drawing
converge at the centre...

543
01:04:01,030 --> 01:04:03,828
...where the betrayal takes
place. Come closer.

544
01:04:03,966 --> 01:04:08,835
Compare the face of Christ to
that of Judas...

545
01:04:08,971 --> 01:04:10,939
...the traitor.

546
01:04:28,991 --> 01:04:32,950
My father isn't a traitor.
He isn't Judas.

547
01:04:41,003 --> 01:04:43,870
SEBASTlANO CANGEMI:
ANOTHER CONFESSION?

548
01:04:44,006 --> 01:04:47,965
NO NEWS OF HIS SON'S
WHEREABOUTS

549
01:04:59,021 --> 01:05:00,989
Stop!

550
01:05:03,960 --> 01:05:06,827
- Go left.
- You want me to drive through
the city?

551
01:05:06,963 --> 01:05:08,931
Could you take a left?

552
01:05:18,975 --> 01:05:21,842
We'll move into a nice hotel.
Just the two of us.

553
01:05:21,978 --> 01:05:24,845
Your uncle wants you to
get a change of scenery.

554
01:05:24,981 --> 01:05:27,950
I've got a wonderful surprise
planned for you.

555
01:05:29,986 --> 01:05:31,954
Vincenzo...

556
01:05:38,995 --> 01:05:41,964
You see that?
Look, it's your sisters!

557
01:05:57,013 --> 01:05:58,981
Mommy!

558
01:06:13,963 --> 01:06:15,828
Be brave!

559
01:06:15,965 --> 01:06:18,832
Is this the appreciation I
get for surprising you?

560
01:06:18,968 --> 01:06:22,927
I showed you them so that
you could see that they're fine!
Everything's fine!

561
01:06:24,974 --> 01:06:26,942
Speed up!

562
01:07:12,955 --> 01:07:14,820
This is for us.

563
01:07:14,957 --> 01:07:18,825
- All of it?
- You can choose whichever ones you want.

564
01:07:18,961 --> 01:07:22,920
- That one, or that one, or that one...
- What if I want to use all of them?

565
01:07:28,971 --> 01:07:30,939
Bon appetit!

566
01:07:54,997 --> 01:07:56,965
How many do you want?

567
01:08:00,002 --> 01:08:02,903
- How many?
- Two!

568
01:08:06,942 --> 01:08:08,913
Goodnight, Rocco!

569
01:08:13,949 --> 01:08:16,918
Not with bare feet I can't!

570
01:08:18,954 --> 01:08:22,822
Come on, today we're playing
against Brazil!

571
01:08:22,958 --> 01:08:26,917
This is how Pelé got started,
when he was a boy. Let's play!

572
01:08:32,968 --> 01:08:36,836
- I play better with shoes!
- Shoes come later!

573
01:08:36,972 --> 01:08:39,839
You need to feel the ball
with your skin, that's how...

574
01:08:39,975 --> 01:08:42,842
...it gets in your blood.
Now pay attention! The ball!

575
01:08:42,978 --> 01:08:45,947
Let's go!
Let's go!

576
01:08:53,989 --> 01:08:55,854
Go away!

577
01:08:55,991 --> 01:08:58,858
Well I didn't have fun, either.

578
01:08:58,994 --> 01:09:01,895
We've got to have patience,
the two of us.

579
01:09:03,933 --> 01:09:05,901
It's just a matter of days.

580
01:09:07,937 --> 01:09:09,802
Don't you trust your dad?

581
01:09:09,939 --> 01:09:11,804
Him, you, and me...

582
01:09:11,941 --> 01:09:14,910
aren't we all a big family?

583
01:09:16,946 --> 01:09:18,914
Let's get back to playing.

584
01:09:27,957 --> 01:09:30,926
Without the 500 Liras, it doesn't work.

585
01:09:32,962 --> 01:09:34,930
Thanks.

586
01:09:42,972 --> 01:09:44,837
Look.

587
01:09:44,974 --> 01:09:48,842
Come on, look. You know what
that mountain is called?

588
01:09:48,978 --> 01:09:52,846
Ballaró.
You know who Ballaró was?

589
01:09:52,982 --> 01:09:54,847
An abductee, like you.

590
01:09:54,984 --> 01:09:57,851
It bears his name, because
he stayed on that mountain.

591
01:09:57,987 --> 01:10:00,956
He never went back home.

592
01:10:02,992 --> 01:10:04,857
But you...

593
01:10:04,994 --> 01:10:08,862
...you're at a great hotel.
You're an artist.

594
01:10:08,998 --> 01:10:10,863
I already told you.

595
01:10:11,000 --> 01:10:14,868
By summer, you and your
sister will be in Cefalú,...

596
01:10:15,004 --> 01:10:16,972
...cheering me on in a discotheque!

597
01:10:19,008 --> 01:10:22,876
- He never went back home?
- Never.

598
01:10:23,012 --> 01:10:26,880
You should know your history.

599
01:10:27,016 --> 01:10:28,984
I don't want to hear it.

600
01:10:32,021 --> 01:10:32,988
Let's play.

601
01:10:35,024 --> 01:10:37,891
Yes, with shoes.
With shoes!

602
01:10:38,027 --> 01:10:40,894
Let's go! Get the ball!
Throw it!

603
01:10:41,030 --> 01:10:42,998
Let's go!

604
01:11:25,007 --> 01:11:27,976
ONE HUNDRED YEARS AGO...

605
01:11:39,021 --> 01:11:40,886
Doctor Ballaró!

606
01:11:41,023 --> 01:11:42,991
Doctor Ballaró.

607
01:11:46,028 --> 01:11:47,996
On your knees.

608
01:11:52,034 --> 01:11:54,002
Are you trying to abduct me?

609
01:12:30,005 --> 01:12:33,873
- No screaming.
- Jesus Christ, a trap!
- Don't blaspheme!

610
01:12:34,009 --> 01:12:37,968
- Now we're in mortal danger!
- They're watching us!

611
01:12:47,022 --> 01:12:48,887
Damn it!

612
01:12:49,024 --> 01:12:50,889
I'm not moving from this spot.

613
01:12:51,026 --> 01:12:52,891
I am not moving from this spot!

614
01:12:53,028 --> 01:12:55,895
I can't do any more. I'm sick.

615
01:12:56,031 --> 01:12:59,000
I'm not moving from this spot.
I'm not moving from this spot.

616
01:13:16,985 --> 01:13:19,852
- Now be good, and write.
- How much do you want?

617
01:13:19,988 --> 01:13:23,856
- A thousand, at least.
- More! More!
- More, of course.

618
01:13:23,992 --> 01:13:25,857
But I don't have any cash.

619
01:13:25,994 --> 01:13:28,861
They'll have to sell their
land, their houses.

620
01:13:28,997 --> 01:13:31,864
If I say here,
what will do you?

621
01:13:32,000 --> 01:13:33,865
They'll borrow it.

622
01:13:34,002 --> 01:13:36,869
- Who will?
- Your mother and your sisters.

623
01:13:37,005 --> 01:13:39,872
My second wife, you mean.

624
01:13:40,008 --> 01:13:42,875
The sisters are hers, not mine.

625
01:13:43,011 --> 01:13:45,878
You messed up, boys.

626
01:13:46,014 --> 01:13:47,879
You messed up.

627
01:13:48,016 --> 01:13:51,884
- You messed up. You got it wrong,
my dear Mannuzzo.
- You recognized me?

628
01:13:52,020 --> 01:13:53,885
My boy...

629
01:13:54,022 --> 01:13:58,891
...you cover your face and
leave your hands uncovered...

630
01:13:59,027 --> 01:14:00,995
...hands that I treated, myself.

631
01:14:02,965 --> 01:14:05,832
Take off that handkerchief,
Mannuzzo.

632
01:14:05,968 --> 01:14:07,833
Look me in the eye.

633
01:14:07,970 --> 01:14:09,835
But how?

634
01:14:09,972 --> 01:14:11,940
How could you do this to me?

635
01:14:14,977 --> 01:14:18,845
Enough talk.
Behave yourself, or we kill you.

636
01:14:18,981 --> 01:14:23,941
You want me to behave?
You're the ones who should be
behaving yourselves!

637
01:14:25,988 --> 01:14:28,855
Come one, what am I supposed
to be writing with?

638
01:14:28,991 --> 01:14:31,858
- A pencil.
- You have one.

639
01:14:31,994 --> 01:14:35,862
- This isn't a pencil...
- Yes, it's a pencil.

640
01:14:35,998 --> 01:14:39,866
You guys don't even know
how to use a pencil.

641
01:14:40,002 --> 01:14:42,869
- What do you mean?
- I mean it needs to have a point!

642
01:14:43,005 --> 01:14:44,870
- Can you sharpen it?
- Yes.

643
01:14:45,007 --> 01:14:48,875
Like this, with the knife.
Sharpening it... with the knife.

644
01:14:49,011 --> 01:14:51,980
No knife!
Behave yourself!

645
01:14:56,018 --> 01:14:59,886
If you want me to write,
I'll write. But it won't matter.

646
01:15:00,022 --> 01:15:03,822
My wife and her sisters
won't respond.

647
01:15:03,959 --> 01:15:07,827
They'll just say they didn't
receive any letter. And... goodbye!

648
01:15:07,963 --> 01:15:10,830
They'd rather I die.

649
01:15:10,966 --> 01:15:13,833
They'd never have killed me.

650
01:15:13,969 --> 01:15:16,836
They were waiting for a miracle
from God...

651
01:15:16,972 --> 01:15:19,839
...sooner or later...

652
01:15:19,975 --> 01:15:22,842
...and that miracle's what
you boys are delivering.

653
01:15:22,978 --> 01:15:25,845
Just send me home. It's
the only solution.

654
01:15:25,981 --> 01:15:28,848
I'll bring you the money.
I know what you're thinking.

655
01:15:28,984 --> 01:15:31,851
"This guy's going to turn us
in, as soon as he gets free."

656
01:15:31,987 --> 01:15:34,854
But really, why should I spend
the little time I have...

657
01:15:34,990 --> 01:15:37,857
...looking over my shoulder
for your avenging relatives?

658
01:15:37,993 --> 01:15:39,858
Rotten wood.

659
01:15:39,995 --> 01:15:42,964
It's shit.

660
01:16:03,952 --> 01:16:05,920
Kill me here.

661
01:16:09,958 --> 01:16:12,825
Kill me here,
with my eyes open.

662
01:16:12,961 --> 01:16:15,828
Don't kill me in my sleep,
that's cowardly.

663
01:16:15,964 --> 01:16:17,829
You don't have any
other options.

664
01:16:17,966 --> 01:16:20,935
Doctor, get inside, or I'll
shoot you.

665
01:16:22,971 --> 01:16:23,938
Fillicó.

666
01:16:25,974 --> 01:16:28,943
Fillicó.
Fillicó.

667
01:16:30,979 --> 01:16:34,938
You're Fillicó?
I'm lost.

668
01:16:36,985 --> 01:16:41,945
I know you, you're a good man.

669
01:16:43,992 --> 01:16:46,859
A beast of burden. A man of integrity.

670
01:16:46,995 --> 01:16:48,963
A man of few words.

671
01:16:52,000 --> 01:16:54,969
How were they able to
strip you of your decency?

672
01:16:57,005 --> 01:16:58,870
How?
How?

673
01:16:59,007 --> 01:17:00,872
Get in, or I'll shoot you.

674
01:17:01,009 --> 01:17:04,809
As sure as the stars in the sky,
I'll shoot you.

675
01:17:04,946 --> 01:17:08,814
Where are these stars you see?
You're a beast.

676
01:17:08,950 --> 01:17:11,817
Beast!
You know nothing...

677
01:17:11,953 --> 01:17:15,821
...and you want to speak of
stars? What stars do you see?

678
01:17:15,957 --> 01:17:18,824
You see them, you think that
they're still there?

679
01:17:18,960 --> 01:17:21,827
You think they haven't
disappeared millions of years ago?

680
01:17:21,963 --> 01:17:23,828
They're dead.
Dead!

681
01:17:23,965 --> 01:17:26,832
If you know nothing about
the things that you see...

682
01:17:26,968 --> 01:17:29,937
...then with what right do
you keep me here?

683
01:17:32,974 --> 01:17:34,942
Let me go.

684
01:18:09,945 --> 01:18:12,812
I came here, sir...

685
01:18:12,948 --> 01:18:16,816
...to tell you that these
three boys of mine...

686
01:18:16,952 --> 01:18:20,820
...have made a mistake,
and repent of their errors.

687
01:18:20,956 --> 01:18:25,825
But they can't let you go.
Nor can they kill you.

688
01:18:25,961 --> 01:18:31,831
They will keep you here,
until God wills it otherwise.

689
01:18:31,967 --> 01:18:33,832
He shall forgive us.

690
01:18:33,969 --> 01:18:39,839
Great sacrifices are in store for you.
And for them as well.

691
01:18:39,975 --> 01:18:44,844
They have resigned themselves
to the punishment they have earned.

692
01:18:44,980 --> 01:18:49,849
Every day, they will bring you
bread and something you eat.

693
01:18:49,985 --> 01:18:53,853
One by one, they will stand
guard over you.

694
01:18:53,989 --> 01:18:56,856
And the other two will work for him.

695
01:18:56,992 --> 01:19:02,794
I brought you this wool coat,
for when it gets cold...

696
01:19:02,931 --> 01:19:05,900
...and this lamp, for when
it gets dark.

697
01:19:08,937 --> 01:19:12,805
The Fontevalle Tabernacle has two.

698
01:19:12,941 --> 01:19:16,809
Up here, we are all Christs
on the cross.

699
01:19:16,945 --> 01:19:18,810
I have to shit!

700
01:19:18,947 --> 01:19:23,907
And I have shit here, on my
feet, like an animal?

701
01:19:27,956 --> 01:19:30,925
Remove his chain.
Let's go.

702
01:19:41,970 --> 01:19:44,939
Come outside.
Come on, get out.

703
01:19:54,983 --> 01:19:57,850
In front of you all?

704
01:19:57,986 --> 01:20:00,955
Make yourself comfortable,
we'll turn around.

705
01:20:13,001 --> 01:20:14,866
I don't know if you were joking
the other night...

706
01:20:15,003 --> 01:20:17,870
...when I said that the stars
are both there and not there...

707
01:20:18,006 --> 01:20:20,975
...and that the eyes see
things that aren't there.

708
01:20:23,011 --> 01:20:26,970
They're not there anymore, Fillicó.
I wasn't joking.

709
01:20:29,017 --> 01:20:31,884
In order to reach us,
the light from those stars...

710
01:20:32,020 --> 01:20:34,887
...has to travel millions
of kilometers...

711
01:20:35,023 --> 01:20:36,888
...over millions of years.

712
01:20:37,025 --> 01:20:43,897
By the time their light has
reached us, the stars themselves
have disappeared from the universe.

713
01:20:44,032 --> 01:20:46,899
- That's how it is, Fillicó.
- What?

714
01:20:47,035 --> 01:20:49,902
Light runs, like a horse?

715
01:20:50,038 --> 01:20:52,905
At millions of kilometers a second.

716
01:20:53,041 --> 01:20:55,009
You're joking.

717
01:20:58,046 --> 01:21:01,948
I wasn't joking then,
and I'm not joking now.

718
01:21:03,985 --> 01:21:07,853
You played a joke on Fillicó.
Light doesn't travel.

719
01:21:07,989 --> 01:21:10,856
It's easy to play a joke on him.
He'll believe anything.

720
01:21:10,992 --> 01:21:14,860
The moon, the stars,
the Milky Way, the scorpions.

721
01:21:14,996 --> 01:21:16,861
They're all witchcraft.

722
01:21:16,998 --> 01:21:20,866
I'm like Saint Thomas.
I only believe in what I touch...

723
01:21:21,002 --> 01:21:22,970
...and in what I see.

724
01:21:27,008 --> 01:21:28,976
Come here.

725
01:21:36,017 --> 01:21:37,882
Your eyes...

726
01:21:38,019 --> 01:21:40,886
...what do they see over there?

727
01:21:41,022 --> 01:21:43,889
- The mountain, and the sky.
- What colour are they?

728
01:21:44,025 --> 01:21:45,890
White.

729
01:21:46,027 --> 01:21:48,996
And now what do you see?

730
01:21:52,033 --> 01:21:55,002
- The sky is green.
- Green.

731
01:22:02,978 --> 01:22:05,845
- And now?
- Red, like Hell.

732
01:22:05,981 --> 01:22:07,846
Red, like Hell.

733
01:22:07,983 --> 01:22:10,850
Your eyes, and mine...

734
01:22:10,986 --> 01:22:14,854
...are like a glass through
which we observe things.

735
01:22:14,990 --> 01:22:18,949
If their colours change, then
so do the things we see.

736
01:22:20,996 --> 01:22:22,861
Think about that.

737
01:22:22,998 --> 01:22:27,867
Things are not they way you're
used to seeing them...

738
01:22:28,003 --> 01:22:32,963
...but also the way you
want to see them, Mannuzzo.

739
01:22:35,010 --> 01:22:36,978
Think about that.

740
01:23:15,984 --> 01:23:19,852
Only animals like you
are ignorant that the earth...

741
01:23:19,988 --> 01:23:22,855
...spins like a top.
Around and around.

742
01:23:22,991 --> 01:23:26,859
Do you mean that, right now...

743
01:23:26,995 --> 01:23:31,864
...there are men standing upside
down, who don't fall into the sky?

744
01:23:32,000 --> 01:23:33,865
- Yes, sir.
- That's incredible!

745
01:23:34,002 --> 01:23:36,869
I don't believe it.

746
01:23:37,005 --> 01:23:40,873
Believe it, my boy.
You are glass...

747
01:23:41,009 --> 01:23:45,878
...glass that God has not yet blown.

748
01:23:46,014 --> 01:23:49,973
Why don't you try to blow me?

749
01:23:57,025 --> 01:23:58,890
Stand over there.

750
01:23:59,027 --> 01:24:00,892
You are this...

751
01:24:01,029 --> 01:24:04,829
...and this is the Earth.
Understand?

752
01:24:04,966 --> 01:24:08,834
The world spins quickly, like so.

753
01:24:08,970 --> 01:24:10,835
Around and around.

754
01:24:10,972 --> 01:24:13,839
- And you don't fall out.
- Doctor, are you trying to kill me?

755
01:24:13,975 --> 01:24:16,944
That's what Galileo said!
Galileo!

756
01:24:51,012 --> 01:24:52,877
Spinning around...

757
01:24:53,014 --> 01:24:54,982
...and around.

758
01:25:32,987 --> 01:25:34,852
A loaf of bread.

759
01:25:34,989 --> 01:25:38,948
Is this your little boy?
What's his name?

760
01:25:40,995 --> 01:25:42,963
Galileo.

761
01:25:44,999 --> 01:25:45,966
Galileo?

762
01:25:48,002 --> 01:25:49,970
Galileo.

763
01:25:52,006 --> 01:25:54,873
- How many children does Mannuzzo have?
- Three.

764
01:25:55,009 --> 01:25:58,877
- Three. And Chicché?
- Five.

765
01:25:59,013 --> 01:26:03,814
Poor Chicché!
Bring them to see me!

766
01:26:03,952 --> 01:26:06,921
I'd like to get to know them,
one of these Sundays.

767
01:26:08,957 --> 01:26:09,924
If I last long enough.

768
01:27:25,967 --> 01:27:29,926
- What happened?
- He's been like this all day.

769
01:27:42,984 --> 01:27:46,852
Leave him. Dr. Ballaró
is a good Christian...

770
01:27:46,988 --> 01:27:49,957
...but a difficult man
to understand.

771
01:28:39,974 --> 01:28:42,841
- It had to be red.
- What?

772
01:28:42,977 --> 01:28:45,842
- The handkerchief.
- Red? Why?

773
01:28:45,979 --> 01:28:47,846
- You're an animal.
- You put it on.

774
01:28:47,982 --> 01:28:50,849
Right, when we kidnapped him...

775
01:28:50,985 --> 01:28:53,954
...it was red.

776
01:29:20,948 --> 01:29:24,907
The kids want to play.
Let's go! Let's go!

